(2) Three active homebuilders, licensed in this state appointed by the president of
the Louisiana Home Builders Association.
(3) Two representatives of the Louisiana Home Builders Association appointed by
the president of that association, one of whom is active in the business of heating,
ventilation, and air conditioning.
(4) One representative of the Police Jury Association of Louisiana appointed by the
president of that association.
(5) One representative of the Louisiana Municipal Association appointed by the
president of that association.
(6) One representative of the Department of Insurance appointed by the
commissioner of insurance.
(7) One representative of the State Licensing Board for Contractors appointed by the
chairman of the board.
(8) One member of the Building Officials Association of Louisiana appointed by its
president.
(9) One active licensed private inspector of the Louisiana Association of Third-Party
Inspectors appointed by its president.
(10) Two active homebuilders appointed by the speaker of the House of
Representatives.
(11) One member of the Louisiana chapter of the American Institute of Architects
appointed by the president of that chapter.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that each appointing authority shall submit the
names of the appointees of the task force to the Louisiana State Uniform Construction Code
Council no later than July 1, 2026.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that at the first meeting, the members shall elect a
chairman and other officers as the task force may deem appropriate.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the task force shall convene for its first meeting
no later than August 1, 2026, at the call of the Louisiana Uniform Construction Code
Council.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the task force shall be staffed by the Louisiana
State Uniform Construction Code Council.
